humanMachineDialogue.text: The report mentions that six out of nineteen lymph nodes are positive for metastatic carcinoma. This puts the patient in N2 stage, which is defined as 'Metastasis in 4 to 9 axillary lymph nodes, or in clinically apparent ipsilateral internal mammary nodes in the absence of axillary lymph node metastasis.'. The mention of extranodal tumor extension also supports this staging.
